Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, python3, python3-gi,
 init-system-helpers (>= 1.66~)
Description: Ambient light / color sensor support for Surface Laptop 7 (X Elite)
 On Snapdragon X Elite laptops the ambient light sensor is not on any
 host-visible bus: it hangs off the Qualcomm Sensor Core (SSC) running on
 the ADSP, and the DSP firmware reads its sensor configuration (wiring,
 factory calibration) from the host filesystem at runtime over FastRPC.
 Windows provides that file service; Linux does not — so the SSC boots
 empty and no sensors exist.
 .
 This package provides the missing pieces: a FastRPC file service attached
 to the sensors protection domain (adsprpcd, built from Qualcomm's open
 source userspace) serving the sensor configuration extracted from the
 machine's own Windows partition via 'sl7-sensors setup' (the files are
 not redistributable), a net.hadess.SensorProxy D-Bus daemon so desktop
 auto-brightness works without IIO hardware (with an optional built-in
 backlight controller), and command-line sensor readers
 ('sl7-sensors lux' / 'sl7-sensors color').
 .
 Developed on the Surface Laptop 7; the mechanism should apply to other
 X Elite machines whose Windows install carries an snscfg driver package.
